Here is a summary of the provided text:

**The Whisper of the Redwoods**

The story follows Mira, a girl who can communicate with trees through feelings. She warns the local rangers that Grandfather Cedar feels "fire," but they dismiss her concerns due to the wet season. Mira realizes the threat is not an external wildfire, but an internal rot spreading through the roots. She rallies the village children to treat the sick trees with a sap and herb mixture. When a small, accidental fire breaks out later that summer, the healthy trees resist the flames, and the rangers contain the fire. Mira feels gratitude from the forest, realizing the trees were warning them of the rot all along.